materials_text: {"blocks":[{"key":"a8td","text":"Reagent Needed: ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":0,"length":16}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"6akmg","text":"DPBS no calcium not magnesium Cat.14190144 ","type":"ordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"ei639","text":"Trypsin-EDTA (0.25%) Cat. 25200056","type":"ordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"dac9i","text":"Knockout SR (Serum Replacement for ESCs/iPSCs) Cat.10828010","type":"ordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"9gcgj","text":"Sterile Corning Falcon Cell Strainer 70µm","type":"ordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"be0s9","text":"Falcon 5mL Round Polystyrene sorting tube with strainer snap cap Cat. 352235 ","type":"ordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

status.info: We use this protocol and it's working.

steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"cr0aa","text":"Add 2mL Trypsin to the 60mm dishes and incubate for 2mins to lift the cells","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"bipth","text":"Add 2ml complete medium to stop trypsinization, and pipette up and down to collect all cells","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"6cah4","text":"Transfer all cell suspension into a 15ml conical tube, spin down to get the cell pellet 200g for 4min","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"ab64c","text":"Resuspend each cell pellet in 1ml sorting medium (Add 2% (vol/vol) KnockOut serum replacement to 50 ml of DPBS. Can be stored at 4 °C for 6 weeks.) ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"5frco","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"c75uc","text":"To make 50 mL add 1mL of KnockOut serum into 49mL DPBS","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"bsol1","text":"Prime the cell strainer with 2mL of sorting medium making sure to cover the entire mesh.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"4j4hb","text":"Apply each cell suspension to the center of a cell strainer (pushing through with pipette where necessary, and – with a new tip – pulling off strained cell suspension stuck to the bottom of filter).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"crs6q","text":"After straining the cell suspension, add about 5µL of sorting medium to wash the strainer for any left-over cells.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"9ke3g","text":"Aliquot cell suspension into sorting tubes and put it on ice.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"5i8v8","text":"Add DAPI (diluted 1:10,000 to make final concentration at 0.1ug/ml) to the strained cell suspension. This helps to distinguish live from dead cells","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"2f6qi","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"3n8d","text":"0.1µL per 1mL ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":0,"length":14}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.section: To prep for FACS: For each condition,
steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"c9p7l","text":"Take 2 culture tubes with 1 mL sushi expansion medium to catch the sorted cells ","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"97da2","text":"Take 3ml extra sorting medium (in case they ask us to dilute the sample) put everything on ice to take to the FACS facility","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"5vguk","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"74crp","text":"Go to the FACS facility at 149, 5th floor, and ring the bell to be let in.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"sup","offset":33,"length":2}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"9pnfu","text":"(i) Use nozzle 1 (100um)","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"oth","text":"(ii) mCherry detection (blue channel; ex: 587nm; em: 610)","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"6skn8","text":"(iii) Just collect mCherry-positive cells; give them the sushi medium-containing tubes to collect cells","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"c61hp","text":"(iv) Tell them you want to try to get \u003e200,000 cells per condition where possible but prioritize getting through as many samples as possible.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"8n3l","text":"(v) Can keep cold while sorting, or sort at RT (either is fine).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"1asvd","text":"(vi) Can let them know how inclusive/restrictive to be when making gates. Threshold parameters include:","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"fvg4","text":"- sorting for singlets (cells on diagonal); doublets usually indicate 2 cells stuck together","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":33,"length":8}],"data":{}},{"key":"core5","text":"- getting rid of particles that are likely debris.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"6qupn","text":"- selecting the mCherry intensity threshold","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"link","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"guid":"15FECF1E6EE011ED8AD10A58A9FEAC02","url":null}}}}
